==English==
===Etymology===
The idea of ''[[integer]]'' here is that the coefficient of the <math>x^2</math> term is 1.
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{mathematics}} A number (real or complex) which is a solution to an equation of the form <math>x^2 + Bx + C = 0</math> for some integers ''B'' and ''C''.  For example 42, or 2+3''i'', or <math>1+\sqrt -3 \over 2</math>.
